All Progressives Congress (APC) National Leader, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, has felicitated Senate President Ahmed Lawan on his 63rd birthday. In a statement yesterday in Lagos by his media aide, Tunde Rahman, the former Lagos State governor described Lawan as a leader who is quietly, but firmly making the desired impact within the polity. He applauded the Senate President for his “immense contributions” to nation-building and for firmly making the desired impact in deepening democracy and entrenching good governance in the country. “An intellectual, prominent politician and experienced parliamentarian, the Senate President has contributed immensely to nation-building. “Through his fine leadership as Chairman of National Assembly and President of the Senate, the parliament has helped President Muhammadu Buhari and the nation to navigate difficult moments.   Encomiums for Senate President Lawan at 63     2019 Report: Works Ministry to recover N1.174b from…     Court defers hearing in suit against Abba Kyari’s…   - Advertisement - Read Also: “Working in concert with House of Representatives Speaker Femi Gbajabiamila, Senator Lawan has maintained a harmonious relationship between the Legislature and the Executive, thus fostering national stability. “Under his watch, the National Assembly also passed some important Bills, like Petroleum Industry Bill and many other Bills which had eluded their predecessors,” the statement said. Asiwaju Tinubu congratulated Lawan and prayed for his good health and renewed energy to enable him to continue to contribute meaningfully to nation-building. “I rejoice with Senator Lawan, his family, colleagues in the Senate and his constituents in Yobe State on his 63rd birthday. “I wish him many more years, good health, renewed energy and increased wisdom to continue to contribute meaningfully to nation-building,” he said.